Source: https://github.com/cornellsh/codex-proxy
License: MIT (see https://github.com/cornellsh/codex-proxy/blob/main/LICENSE)

The Python files in this directory are verbatim copies of the relevant
modules from cornellsh/codex-proxy@main. They are kept here as documentation
ONLY — for porting to Rust inside src-tauri/src/relay_translate.rs. They are
not compiled into the codex-switcher binary.

When porting, retain the same algorithmic decisions:
- normalizer.py    — codex /v1/responses → OpenAI Chat messages array
- zai_provider.py  — payload preparation, tool transformations, sync response mapping
- zai_stream.py    — SSE event mapping (chat completion deltas → Responses events)

Files:
- normalizer.py    (verbatim, comments stripped for brevity)
- zai_provider.py  (verbatim, comments stripped for brevity)
- zai_stream.py    (verbatim, comments stripped for brevity)
